description: A replication set replicates and encrypts your data to the provided Regions with the provided KMS key.

parameters.name: clientToken
parameters.description: A token that ensures that the operation is called only once with the specified details. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

parameters.name: regions
parameters.description: The Regions that Incident Manager replicates your data to. You can have up to three Regions in your replication set. (string) --- (dict) --- The mapping between a Amazon Web Services Region and the key that's used to encrypt the data. sseKmsKeyId (string) --- The KMS key used to encrypt the data in your replication set.

nested_params.name: sseKmsKeyId
nested_params.description: The KMS key used to encrypt the data in your replication set.

parameters.name: tags
parameters.description: A list of tags to add to the replication set. (string) --- (string) ---

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the replication set.
